==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chigre
<hw>Chig"re</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>chigue</ets>, perh. fr. Catalan
<ets>chic</ets> small, Sp. <ets>chico</ets>; or of Peruvian
origin.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A species of flea (<spn>Tunga
penetrans</spn>, formerly <spn>Pulex penetrans</spn>), common in the
West Indies and South America, which often attacks the feet or any
exposed part of the human body, and burrowing beneath the skin produces
great irritation. When the female is allowed to remain and breed,
troublesome sores result, which are sometimes dangerous. See
<er>Jigger</er>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>chegre</asp>,
<asp>chegoe</asp>, <asp>chique</asp>, <asp>chigger</asp>,
<asp>jigger</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is sometimes erroneously given to certain mites
or ticks having similar habits.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chih fu</ent>⟦br⟧
